NAME
    App::govproc::pericmd - Perinci::CmdLine-based variant of govproc CLI

VERSION
    This document describes version 0.001 of App::govproc::pericmd (from
    Perl distribution App-govproc-pericmd), released on 2019-05-22.

SYNOPSIS
    See the included script govproc-pericmd.

DESCRIPTION
    This distribution carries govproc-pericmd, the govproc CLI utility based
    on Perinci::CmdLine, mainly for testing. Normal users should still use
    the official govproc from Proc::Govern that is lighter and has fewer
    dependencies.

HOMEPAGE
    Please visit the project's homepage at
    <https://metacpan.org/release/App-govproc-pericmd>.

SOURCE
    Source repository is at
    <https://github.com/perlancar/perl-App-govproc-pericmd>.

BUGS
    Please report any bugs or feature requests on the bugtracker website
    <https://rt.cpan.org/Public/Dist/Display.html?Name=App-govproc-pericmd>

    When submitting a bug or request, please include a test-file or a patch
    to an existing test-file that illustrates the bug or desired feature.

